{
  "_comment": "Pre-extracted terms from early MIGS Word documents. These documents have complex table structures that require manual interpretation.",
  "_extraction_method": "Terms were extracted by Claude Code through interactive analysis of the Word document table structures. The python-docx library was used to read raw table data, which was then manually interpreted to identify term names, definitions, sections, and checklist requirements. This approach was necessary because the Word documents use a non-standard table layout with merged cells, section headers mixed with data rows, and abbreviated term descriptions that require human/AI interpretation to normalize into structured term names.",
